fields.title: Uncle from Another World
fields.review: Its story about the someone who go into isekai and back to real world after few years in isekai, the story about uncle that try to live normally in current real world who basically different than isekai world and the world he used to be. Its RESERVE ISEKAI okay? its good

fields.title: Overlord IV
fields.review: Overlord is a truly amazing show that takes you to this whole new world of fantasy. Every character is so unique and intresting in their own way, the world building and build up is absolutely amazing and the plot is so intrieging. I recommend this show to everyone who loves fantasy.

fields.title: The Devil is a Part-Timer! Season 2
fields.review: Season 2 of The Devil is a Part Timer has been getting some pretty serious criticism from fans, and I think a lot of it is pretty deserved.

fields.title: If Her Flag Breaks
fields.review: The concept of flags seems interesting right? Death flags, friendship flags, even a romance flag to top it all off. The low score this anime has is something I strongly disagree with.

fields.title: Restaurant to Another World 2
fields.review: Have you ever come home, from school, or from a long days work, to either a nice warm cooked meal, or just a nice and lovely treat that has been prepared for you, and is waiting for you. That is the general feeling when it comes to this show.

fields.title: Komi Can't Communicate
fields.review: If you were to ask if Komi could represent a realistic human being, then the answer is yes, and you have to look no further than yours truly.

fields.title: The Detective Is Already Dead
fields.review: Between the good anime and the enjoyably bad anime sit the ones that are unremarkable in every way, and you can’t help but wish you hadn’t wasted your time watching it. The Detective is Already Dead fits this role perfectly.

fields.title: The World Ends with You The Animation
fields.review: The story is definitely there. It had some decent mystery (who the MC is, who the composer, what the f*ck is happening, etch.) but because of the fast pace of this anime, the reveal of these mysteries are kinda lackluster and definitely not good.

fields.title: Log Horizon: Destruction of the Round Table
fields.review: A wonderful continuation of one of the best anime yet on the subject of lost other worlds and games, it ha style, great characters, fine and well done art and design and overall a joy to watch.

fields.title: Grimgar: Ashes and Illusions
fields.review: Many misunderstand what the show is really about and what it's trying to be. They complain, just when will they get over with this and go start adventuring?!, and claim, nothing is happening bs!, what they didn't know is it's not aimed to be that.
